                <h1>Context Technology</h1><p>AVEVA's Information Management technology unlocks immense value from the <a href="/en/Digital-Asset.aspx">Digital Asset</a> by providing access to the right information, in the right place, at the right time, to improve decision-making speed and accuracy.</p>
                <p>Context technology puts this rich information resource literally at the fingertips of the designer or engineer. Direct ‘in-context’ retrieval of relevant content from the Digital Asset speeds up their decision-making, without having to leave their standard applications.</p>
                <p><a href="/en/Products_and_Services/Product_Finder/AVEVA_E3D.aspx?tab=4" class="fancy" onclick="javascript: return false;">AVEVA E3D</a>, <a href="/en/Products_and_Services/Product_Finder/AVEVA_Diagrams.aspx?tab=3" class="fancy" onclick="javascript: return false;">AVEVA Diagrams</a> and <a href="/en/Products_and_Services/Product_Finder/AVEVA_Engineering.aspx?tab=4" class="fancy" onclick="javascript: return false;">AVEVA Engineering</a> are the first products to benefit from this new technology, that embeds a multi-format document viewer to give them a window into the Digital Asset.</p>
            </div><h2></h2><div id="tabs">
                <ul class="tab-nav"><li class="active"><a href="#tab-1" class="tab-nav-control">How it looks</a></li><li><a href="#tab-2" class="tab-nav-control">How it works</a></li></ul><div class="tab-content" id="tab-1" style="display: block;">
                    <p>AVEVA has implemented Context Technology as <strong>Design in Context</strong>. This example shows Design in Context for the 3D designer:</p>
                    <p style="text-align: center;"><a href="/~/media/Aveva/English/Products/Images/E3D/E3D-in-Context.png?la=en" target="_blank" title="View in a new window"><img alt="Design in Context" src="/~/media/Aveva/English/Products/Images/E3D/E3D-in-Context.png?h=276&amp;w=420&amp;la=en" style="height: 276px; width: 420px; vertical-align: middle; border-width: 0px; border-style: solid;"></a></p>
                    <p>A selected object's data sheet or other information can be quickly displayed to support a design decision.</p>
                    <h2>Learn more:</h2>
                    <p><a href="/en/Products_and_Services/Product_Finder/AVEVA_E3D.aspx?tab=4" class="button_webinar fancy" onclick="javascript: return false;">AVEVA E3D</a> <a href="/en/Products_and_Services/Product_Finder/AVEVA_Diagrams.aspx?tab=3" class="button_webinar fancy" onclick="javascript: return false;">AVEVA Diagrams</a> <a href="/en/Products_and_Services/Product_Finder/AVEVA_Engineering.aspx?tab=4" class="button_webinar fancy" onclick="javascript: return false;">AVEVA Engineering</a></p>
                </div><div class="tab-content" id="tab-2" style="display: none;">
                    <p>Design in Context integrates <a href="/en/Products_and_Services/Product_Finder/AVEVA_NET_Workhub-Dashboard.aspx" class="fancy" onclick="javascript: return false;">AVEVA NET</a> into the engineering and design tools. It makes contextually linked information about any selected tagged object immediately available to the user.</p>
                    <p>Nearly half of the information project engineers and designers need is created and managed outside of the design environment. So they can spend up to 20% of their time gathering and reviewing it.</p>
                    <p>Now a designer can quickly review all available related information, such as:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Technical specifications</li>
                        <li>Applicable standards</li>
                        <li>Design guides</li>
                        <li>Vendor documentation</li>
                        <li>Procurement status</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>The result is better decision making, fewer errors and a more efficient project.</p>
